00:41:21,808 --> 00:41:26,414
And he used to bring photos home
with pictures in them.

535
00:41:26,643 --> 00:41:27,985
And in the evening,
he'd put on his traveling coat.

536
00:41:28,339 --> 00:41:30,543
That's what he called it,
'Cause I was very young.

537
00:41:30,740 --> 00:41:32,267
And he'd say:
where should we go this evening?

538
00:41:32,468 --> 00:41:35,665
And I would say: Verra Cruse.
Because it's a beautiful name.

539
00:41:36,021 --> 00:41:38,291
And then he would say: um...
it's summer there,

540
00:41:38,486 --> 00:41:40,908
You don't want to be roasted
like a coffee bean, do you?

541
00:41:41,110 --> 00:41:42,289
So, you never did get there?

542
00:41:42,647 --> 00:41:45,234
No. It's just like I tripped the land
with the midnight sun.

543
00:41:45,624 --> 00:41:46,552
What stop are you in time?

544
00:41:46,745 --> 00:41:47,476
The weather.

545
00:41:47,705 --> 00:41:48,436
I thought of India.

546
00:41:48,633 --> 00:41:50,870
But then father remembered
it was the raining season.

547
00:41:51,066 --> 00:41:52,724
Your father was an expert on climates.

548
00:41:52,923 --> 00:41:53,752
My mother used to say that...

549
00:41:53,947 --> 00:41:57,745
He knew what the weather
was everywhere except home.

550
00:41:58,108 --> 00:41:58,708
What mountain was that?

551
00:41:59,068 --> 00:42:00,891
That's the Mt. MataHorn.

552
00:42:01,085 --> 00:42:02,133
You've climbed it?

553
00:42:02,366 --> 00:42:03,260
Um hum.

554
00:42:03,454 --> 00:42:06,302
Tell me when you've climbed up
the mountain,
what then?

555
00:42:07,936 --> 00:42:13,633
Well, you come down again.

556
00:42:17,187 --> 00:42:19,359
Tell me more about your father.

557
00:42:19,555 --> 00:42:23,867
Well, then he finally did go away.

558
00:42:24,068 --> 00:42:25,443
He had the nicest eyes.

559
00:42:25,797 --> 00:42:28,896
Yes, I can see them.

560
00:42:29,094 --> 00:42:31,233
Why do you like to climb mountains?

561
00:42:31,591 --> 00:42:32,966
Well, I suppose because,

562
00:42:33,160 --> 00:42:36,390
No matter how high you climb,
there's always a higher one.

563
00:42:36,585 --> 00:42:38,952
And you like to imagine
that the other one is even more wond

564
00:42:39,305 --> 00:42:39,687
Like the spring in the park.

565
00:42:39,914 --> 00:42:41,256
You know far too much about me already,

566
00:42:41,449 --> 00:42:44,233
And I know almost nothing about you

567
00:42:44,427 --> 00:42:49,033
Except you traveled a great deal.

568
00:42:54,062 --> 00:42:56,878
All change.

569
00:43:06,417 --> 00:43:07,563
What now?

570
00:43:07,762 --> 00:43:08,777
Where haven't we been?

571
00:43:09,139 --> 00:43:10,994
We have no countries left.

572
00:43:11,187 --> 00:43:13,327
Then we'll begin all over again.

573
00:43:13,556 --> 00:43:17,135
There you are.
Thank you.

574
00:43:17,334 --> 00:43:21,132
We'll revisit the scenes of your youth.

575
00:43:48,607 --> 00:43:50,463
I don't know about them
but I'm going home.

576
00:43:50,656 --> 00:43:51,485
Right after this number.

577
00:43:51,680 --> 00:43:54,583
? Me too, if he is not paying
me 50 quarters.

578
00:43:54,817 --> 00:44:02,010
I'd like to playing for married people.
They've got homes.

579
00:44:11,878 --> 00:44:13,734
You're sorcerous.

580
00:44:13,927 --> 00:44:18,271
Now I'm sure,
How else could we dance this way

581
00:44:18,729 --> 00:44:21,861
Unless we've danced together before.

582
00:44:22,058 --> 00:44:27,755
And if we had,
we should ever remember it.

583
00:44:33,517 --> 00:44:36,366
Please.

584
00:45:10,137 --> 00:45:11,250
Promise me something.

585
00:45:11,450 --> 00:45:13,938
Anything.

586
00:45:14,171 --> 00:45:16,538
But I don't even know where you live.

587
00:45:16,731 --> 00:45:19,033
Promise me you won't vanish.

588
00:45:19,228 --> 00:45:24,926
I won't be the one who vanishes.

589
00:45:47,909 --> 00:45:48,541
We're here.

590
00:45:48,742 --> 00:45:51,590
Thank you.

591
00:46:02,186 --> 00:46:05,001
Thank you.

592
00:46:13,645 --> 00:46:14,507
Who is it?

593
00:46:14,701 --> 00:46:15,596
Brown.

594
00:46:15,790 --> 00:46:20,527
Good morning, Mr. Brown.

595
00:46:24,017 --> 00:46:27,793
(End of Side A)

596
00:47:02,556 --> 00:47:05,874
Please be seated.

597
00:47:06,078 --> 00:47:09,046
Lisa, leave it on.
Someone wants to see it.

598
00:47:09,247 --> 00:47:09,814
Oh.

599
00:47:10,015 --> 00:47:15,713
Real customer. Looks like a good one.

600
00:47:16,450 --> 00:47:19,101
One moment.

601
00:47:21,506 --> 00:47:28,579
You'll like this one, I'm sure.
I'm sure.

602
00:47:30,117 --> 00:47:34,908
I like it very much.
Very much.

603
00:47:35,111 --> 00:47:36,606
How did you find me?

604
00:47:36,840 --> 00:47:38,302
I'm a good detective, what you think?

605
00:47:38,664 --> 00:47:41,513
You are.

606
00:47:47,435 --> 00:47:51,429
I'm afraid we have to put off
our play for tonight.

607
00:47:51,628 --> 00:47:54,280
I couldn't go away without seeing you.

608
00:47:54,477 --> 00:47:55,426
Where are you going?

609
00:47:55,629 --> 00:47:56,874
Milano.

610
00:47:57,070 --> 00:48:00,617
The whole orchestra are going.
We go to play at Chigano.

611
00:48:00,816 --> 00:48:03,053
It's wonderful.

612
00:48:03,248 --> 00:48:06,097
I've forgotten all about it.

613
00:48:06,481 --> 00:48:08,904
It won't be long.
Just two weeks.

614
00:48:09,266 --> 00:48:11,242
The train leaves at 5:30.

615
00:48:11,442 --> 00:48:14,607
Do you suppose you could see me off?

616
00:48:14,804 --> 00:48:15,698
I'll try.

617
00:48:16,052 --> 00:48:22,131
I'll look for you then.
Good bye. Thank you.

618
00:48:23,318 --> 00:48:29,016
Good-bye. You will be there.

619
00:48:29,560 --> 00:48:31,448
How did it go?

620
00:48:31,641 --> 00:48:32,951
He wasn't interested in the suit.

621
00:48:33,306 --> 00:48:36,340
But... Madam,
could I leave a bit earlier today?

622
00:48:36,539 --> 00:48:39,223
How early?
About 5:00.

623
00:48:39,420 --> 00:48:42,039
Yes.
Sure.

624
00:48:42,236 --> 00:48:43,349
Thank you, Madam.

625
00:48:43,549 --> 00:48:48,285
Congratulations, my dear.

626
00:49:08,069 --> 00:49:12,674
Stephan, the train is leaving.
Just a minute

627
00:49:12,870 --> 00:49:16,613
How long have you been standing here?

628
00:49:16,807 --> 00:49:20,256
I don't want to go. Do you believe that?

629
00:49:20,457 --> 00:49:21,951
I'll be here when you get back.

630
00:49:22,313 --> 00:49:22,695
Come on.

631
00:49:22,889 --> 00:49:26,054
Yes.
Stephan, hurry, please.

632
00:49:26,250 --> 00:49:29,120
I still know so little about you.

633
00:49:29,324 --> 00:49:33,035
You like mistery.

634
00:49:33,228 --> 00:49:36,578
That a woman like you exist,
and I found you.

635
00:49:36,782 --> 00:49:39,597
That's mistery to me.

636
00:49:39,790 --> 00:49:43,752
SayStephan,
the way you said it last night.

637
00:49:43,952 --> 00:49:46,473
Stephan.

638
00:49:46,673 --> 00:49:48,135
As if you've said it all your life.

639
00:49:48,337 --> 00:49:48,719
Better hurry, sir.

640
00:49:49,074 --> 00:49:50,765
Yes.

641
00:49:51,122 --> 00:49:51,504
Good-bye.

642
00:49:51,699 --> 00:49:56,010
Stephan.
Good-bye.

643
00:49:56,276 --> 00:50:00,500
Won't be long.
I'll be back in two weeks.

644
00:50:03,606 --> 00:50:07,382
Good-bye. Two weeks.

645
00:50:22,716 --> 00:50:26,874
Two weeks... Stehpan,
how little you knew of yourself.

646
00:50:27,646 --> 00:50:33,344
That train was taking
you out of my life.

647
00:51:08,747 --> 00:51:12,043
He was a married man.

648
00:51:12,236 --> 00:51:16,012
Does he live here in Vienna?

649
00:51:16,397 --> 00:51:17,739
If we knew who he was,

650
00:51:17,934 --> 00:51:23,632
He might be willing
to accept his responsibility.

651
00:51:25,040 --> 00:51:30,738
You won't tell us his name?

652
00:51:34,227 --> 00:51:37,424
But you haven't the means
to take care of the child.

653
00:51:37,620 --> 00:51:41,396
We'll get along.

654
00:51:41,973 --> 00:51:43,501
It's your duty to tell us.

655
00:51:43,702 --> 00:51:44,651
When a man does...

656
00:51:44,854 --> 00:51:50,126
I'm feeling tired.
Would you go?

657
00:51:52,473 --> 00:51:55,376
You may wonder
why I never came to you for help.

658
00:51:55,770 --> 00:51:58,585
I wanted to be one woman
you've had known,

659
00:51:58,811 --> 00:52:01,146
Who had asked you for nothing.

660
00:52:01,532 --> 00:52:05,330
My deep regret is
that you never saw your son.

661
00:52:05,533 --> 00:52:10,291
There were times during those years,
I prefer not to remember.

662
00:52:10,495 --> 00:52:12,437
But this I can assure you,

663
00:52:12,639 --> 00:52:17,496
Whatever the cost,
he'd repayed me a thousand times.

664
00:52:17,857 --> 00:52:20,760
You'd have been proud of him, too.

665
00:52:20,994 --> 00:52:22,849
When he was almost nine.

666
00:52:23,075 --> 00:52:26,753
As much for his sake as mine,
I married.

667
00:52:26,980 --> 00:52:28,803
You know who my husband is.

668
00:52:28,997 --> 00:52:30,885
Yohan Stafe asked to marry me.

669
00:52:31,237 --> 00:52:34,020
Knowing the truth about us,
and about our child.

670
00:52:34,214 --> 00:52:35,261
Oh. How lovely.

671
00:52:35,494 --> 00:52:37,983
Thank you, Yohan.

672
00:52:38,183 --> 00:52:39,558
What a nice birthday!

673
00:52:39,912 --> 00:52:42,084
This..., and Stephan home.

674
00:52:42,281 --> 00:52:44,648
You know,
I'm not good at saying such things.

675
00:52:44,841 --> 00:52:48,901
But... Lisa, I want you to be
as happy as you may be.

676
00:52:49,099 --> 00:52:55,495
If I were really deserving why,
I'll be ready on time.

677
00:52:55,692 --> 00:52:58,541
You are happy?

678
00:53:02,479 --> 00:53:04,105
You are?

679
00:53:04,304 --> 00:53:08,080
Why shouldn't I be?

680
00:53:08,593 --> 00:53:12,369
Let's say Good-night.

681
00:53:15,956 --> 00:53:19,273
Is that your another talent?

682
00:53:19,508 --> 00:53:25,206
He has a lot of talents,
but not until he finishes his milk.

683
00:53:26,903 --> 00:53:28,943
Or for brushing his teeth.

684
00:53:29,144 --> 00:53:30,322
Made in Switzerland.

685
00:53:30,680 --> 00:53:33,550
Switzerland must be a very nice place,
don't you think?

686
00:53:33,753 --> 00:53:34,931
Who gave it to you, darling?

687
00:53:35,129 --> 00:53:35,860
Her Frank.

688
00:53:36,058 --> 00:53:36,952
Who's Her Frank?

689
00:53:37,146 --> 00:53:38,073
His music teacher.

690
00:53:38,426 --> 00:53:40,337
He said that he thinks
that I'm nature talented.

691
00:53:40,572 --> 00:53:41,652
For harmonica?

692
00:53:41,851 --> 00:53:44,121
No. For music.

693
00:53:44,316 --> 00:53:47,000
Oh.

694
00:53:47,197 --> 00:53:48,146
Good night, Stephan.

695
00:53:48,350 --> 00:53:51,318
Good night, sir.

696
00:53:51,519 --> 00:53:52,413
Good night, darling.

697
00:53:52,767 --> 00:53:56,543
Good night, mother.

698
00:53:59,169 --> 00:53:59,736
Mother!

699
00:53:59,970 --> 00:54:00,864
Yes!

700
00:54:01,090 --> 00:54:04,866
I'll be right back.

701
00:54:06,179 --> 00:54:08,668
You remember the last time,
first night I was home from school.

702
00:54:09,028 --> 00:54:10,010
Um-hum, what about it?

703
00:54:10,212 --> 00:54:12,602
When you went out,
you let me sleep in your room.

704
00:54:12,966 --> 00:54:13,281
Alright.

705
00:54:13,477 --> 00:54:15,812
It's a special concession
because it's your first night home

706
00:54:16,006 --> 00:54:19,782
But hurry. I'm late.

707
00:54:23,113 --> 00:54:25,863
In just a minute.
There's no hurry.

708
00:54:26,058 --> 00:54:27,269
Good night, sir.

709
00:54:27,498 --> 00:54:30,314
Good night.

710
00:54:34,349 --> 00:54:36,105
You know, Stephan, it might be nicer...

711
00:54:36,301 --> 00:54:39,368
If you could say Good night,
father!instead ofGood nigh

712
00:54:39,726 --> 00:54:41,101
But I've always said it that way.

713
00:54:41,326 --> 00:54:43,563
I think he'd like it
if you could manage to change it.

714
00:54:43,759 --> 00:54:45,832
Suppose you said to me
Good night, Madam.

715
00:54:46,032 --> 00:54:48,487
It would sound very silly, wouldn't it?

716
00:54:48,689 --> 00:54:51,275
Now, promise me you'd go to sleep,
and not wait up for me.

717
00:54:51,474 --> 00:54:52,402
I promise.

718
00:54:52,594 --> 00:54:54,188
Would you bring me
the program of the opera?

719
00:54:54,387 --> 00:54:57,202
I promise.

720
00:54:58,388 --> 00:55:00,144
Good night, Madam.

721
00:55:00,340 --> 00:55:01,966
Good night, Sir.

722
00:55:02,165 --> 00:55:05,166
After all when a person treats
you so much like his son,

723
00:55:05,398 --> 00:55:07,024
He is make sense of your father.

724
00:55:07,223 --> 00:55:09,198
Alright, mother, if you say so.

725
00:55:09,560 --> 00:55:12,408
Good night.

726
00:55:20,603 --> 00:55:25,044
The course of our lives can
be changed by such little thing

727
00:55:25,245 --> 00:55:29,654
So many passing by,
each intent on his own problems.

728
00:55:29,854 --> 00:55:35,420
So many faces,
that one might be easily lost.

729
00:55:35,615 --> 00:55:39,894
I know now. Nothing happens by chance.

730
00:55:40,289 --> 00:55:46,783
Every moment is measured.
Every step is counted.

731
00:55:46,979 --> 00:55:48,768
Curtain. Curtain going up.

732
00:55:48,964 --> 00:55:49,727
Second act.

733
00:55:49,924 --> 00:55:54,944
Curtain going up. Second act.

734
00:55:55,142 --> 00:55:57,379
Look! Isn't that Stephan Brown?

735
00:55:57,606 --> 00:55:59,844
He played last week.
Is that a concert tour?

736
00:56:00,039 --> 00:56:01,665
Pleasure trip, most likely.

737
00:56:01,864 --> 00:56:08,260
The way he's burning himself up,
it's a wonder he's still alive.

738
00:56:08,459 --> 00:56:11,242
Ten years ago, he showed great promise.

739
00:56:11,435 --> 00:56:12,483
Too bad.

740
00:56:12,875 --> 00:56:15,778
With that talent,
he could've been a great pianist.

741
00:56:15,981 --> 00:56:17,737
Perhaps talent is not enough.

742
00:56:17,933 --> 00:56:20,203
Perhaps he's have too many talents.

743
00:56:20,558 --> 00:56:21,387
Second act!

744
00:56:21,582 --> 00:56:25,358
Curtain going up!

745
00:56:34,258 --> 00:56:35,785
Sorry.

746
00:56:35,987 --> 00:56:36,848
We're late.

747
00:56:37,043 --> 00:56:39,727
You know the colonel is going...

748
00:56:39,924 --> 00:56:41,550
Everyone is asking for you.

749
00:56:41,749 --> 00:56:42,578
You've made a conquest.

750
00:56:42,773 --> 00:56:48,471
My dear, you should have joined this.

751
00:57:07,613 --> 00:57:10,810
Suddenly, in that one moment.

752
00:57:11,006 --> 00:57:12,916
Every thing was in danger.

753
00:57:13,310 --> 00:57:15,799
Every thing I thought was safe.

754
00:57:16,160 --> 00:57:22,304
Somewhere out there were your eyes.
couldn't escape them.Somewhere out there were yo

755
00:57:22,498 --> 00:57:24,986
It's like the first time I saw you.

756
00:57:25,186 --> 00:57:30,622
The years between were melting away.

757
00:57:30,820 --> 00:57:31,486
I have a headache.

758
00:57:31,685 --> 00:57:31,968
I'll take you home.

759
00:57:32,164 --> 00:57:33,092
No. Please don't worry.

760
00:57:33,445 --> 00:57:38,597
I'll be alright.
Please stay here.

761
00:57:51,179 --> 00:57:52,902
Would you be kind enough
to give my husband a message.

762
00:57:53,099 --> 00:57:54,660
He's in 17. Not now.

763
00:57:54,860 --> 00:57:55,808
But after the show.

764
00:57:56,013 --> 00:57:58,053
Tell him, I've decided to go home.
Tell him not to worry.

765
00:57:58,413 --> 00:58:01,229
Thank you.

766
00:58:10,833 --> 00:58:11,815
Call my carriage, please.

767
00:58:12,017 --> 00:58:14,385
Yes, Madam.

768
00:58:14,738 --> 00:58:15,153
Sergeant!

769
00:58:15,378 --> 00:58:18,194
Yes, Madam.

770
00:58:46,940 --> 00:58:48,250
Excuse me.

771
00:58:48,476 --> 00:58:50,550
You must realized
that where there's a pursuit.

772
00:58:50,750 --> 00:58:53,085
And there'd also be a pursuer.

773
00:58:53,278 --> 00:58:56,443
I've seen you somewhere, I know.

774
00:58:56,639 --> 00:58:57,982
I followed you upstairs.

775
00:58:58,176 --> 00:58:59,737
And watched you in your box.

776
00:58:59,937 --> 00:59:02,304
But I couldn't place you.

777
00:59:02,657 --> 00:59:05,790
And I had to speak with you.

778
00:59:05,986 --> 00:59:10,428
I know how it sounds.
I assure you in this case that it's true.

779
00:59:10,660 --> 00:59:12,733
Believe that, don't you?

780
00:59:12,933 --> 00:59:14,756
Yes.
Thank you.

781
00:59:15,110 --> 00:59:16,604
Now please, just a moment.

782
00:59:16,806 --> 00:59:20,189
Is that any place we could have met,
that I might have seen

783
00:59:20,391 --> 00:59:22,945
At one of my concerts?

784
00:59:23,144 --> 00:59:24,738
There must have been sometime ago.

785
00:59:24,968 --> 00:59:28,002
I haven't given any concerts
in Vienna lately.

786
00:59:28,202 --> 00:59:30,788
Or anywhere else in that matter.

787
00:59:30,986 --> 00:59:33,408
You don't play anymore?

788
00:59:33,611 --> 00:59:35,499
Oh, it's not quite as final as that.

789
00:59:35,692 --> 00:59:38,376
I always tell myself that,
Beginning next week.

790
00:59:38,572 --> 00:59:40,613
And when next week comes,
it's this week.

791
00:59:40,974 --> 00:59:42,567
So, I wait for next week again.

792
00:59:42,926 --> 00:59:45,316
What are you waiting for?

793
00:59:45,519 --> 00:59:47,080
It's a very disturbing question.

794
00:59:47,279 --> 00:59:47,879
My carriage...

795
00:59:48,080 --> 00:59:51,496
You can't ask such a question,
and just walk away.

796
00:59:51,697 --> 00:59:54,698
I have a feeling...
please don't think I'm mad.

797
00:59:54,898 --> 00:59:58,444
I know it sounds strange.
I can't explain it.

798
00:59:58,643 --> 01:00:03,565
But I feel that you understand
what I can't even say.

799
01:00:03,765 --> 01:00:07,214
And that you can help me.

800
01:00:07,414 --> 01:00:13,112
Have you ever shopped
for places like cards,

801
01:00:13,656 --> 01:00:14,900
Hoping to find the one...

802
01:00:15,097 --> 01:00:18,643
Lies somewhere at the edge
of your memory.

803
01:00:18,842 --> 01:00:21,876
The one you've been waiting for.

804
01:00:22,234 --> 01:00:24,340
But tonight, when I first saw you.

805
01:00:24,539 --> 01:00:27,093
And later
when I watched you in the darkness.

806
01:00:27,292 --> 01:00:31,865
It looked like one face amongst others.

807
01:00:32,093 --> 01:00:34,909
Who are you?

808
01:00:36,287 --> 01:00:38,676
Promise me, I'll see you again.
I must see you.

809
01:00:38,880 --> 01:00:41,695
I don't know.

810
01:01:03,688 --> 01:01:09,385
Yohan,
you don't think I want this to happen?

811
01:01:10,410 --> 01:01:12,352
What are you going to do?

812
01:01:12,555 --> 01:01:15,370
I don't know.

813
01:01:15,980 --> 01:01:19,810
Lisa. We have a marriage.

814
01:01:20,013 --> 01:01:22,916
Perhaps it's not all you once
hoped for. But...

815
01:01:23,118 --> 01:01:27,145
You've a home, and your son.
People who care for you.

816
01:01:27,503 --> 01:01:29,413
I know that, Yohan.

817
01:01:29,616 --> 01:01:31,307
I'll do anything to avoid hurting you.

818
01:01:31,536 --> 01:01:34,734
But I can't help it.

819
01:01:35,090 --> 01:01:37,196
And your son?

820
01:01:37,394 --> 01:01:39,151
Can you avoid hurting him?

821
01:01:39,347 --> 01:01:44,106
I have to calm down and see that.

822
01:01:44,309 --> 01:01:49,526
There're such things as honor,
and decency.

823
01:01:49,719 --> 01:01:52,054
I told myself that hundred times
this one evening.

824
01:01:52,440 --> 01:01:54,928
You talk like it is out of your hands.

825
01:01:55,288 --> 01:01:58,518
It's not, Lisa.
You have a will.

826
01:01:58,745 --> 01:02:01,681
You can do what's right,
what's best for you.

827
01:02:02,043 --> 01:02:04,148
Or you can throw away your life.

828
01:02:04,347 --> 01:02:06,769
I have no hopes whatsoever.

829
01:02:06,972 --> 01:02:08,761
That's romantic nonsense.

830
01:02:08,957 --> 01:02:10,386
Is it?

831
01:02:10,749 --> 01:02:11,731
Yohan, I can't help it.

832
01:02:11,933 --> 01:02:14,073
I can't dispute that.

833
01:02:14,270 --> 01:02:19,542
What about him?
Can him help himself, either?

834
01:02:20,608 --> 01:02:24,384
I know now that he needs me
as much as I always needed him.

835
01:02:24,609 --> 01:02:27,807
Isn't it a bit late for him
to find that out?

836
01:02:28,002 --> 01:02:31,778
We're home, sir.

837
01:02:41,671 --> 01:02:42,751
Good night.

838
01:02:42,951 --> 01:02:46,727
Good night, sir.

839
01:02:59,628 --> 01:03:04,845
Lisa. If you do this,
you can never turn back.

840
01:03:05,038 --> 01:03:06,315
You know that, don't you?

841
01:03:06,511 --> 01:03:09,326
Yes.

842
01:03:13,265 --> 01:03:17,423
I warn you. I shall do everything in
my power to prevent it.

843
01:03:48,797 --> 01:03:50,139
Hello, darling. Wake up.

844
01:03:51,357 --> 01:03:57,055
It's time to go to your own room.

845
01:03:59,231 --> 01:04:01,021
Did you have a nice time?

846
01:04:01,216 --> 01:04:04,032
Yes, darling.

847
01:04:04,897 --> 01:04:06,392
Good night, father.

848
01:04:06,754 --> 01:04:08,642
Good night.

849
01:04:08,834 --> 01:04:10,558
Did you hear? I just said it.

850
01:04:10,755 --> 01:04:12,610
Yes, darling.

851
01:04:12,804 --> 01:04:18,502
Tell me about the opera...
was it exciting?

852
01:04:24,424 --> 01:04:25,056
How's that?

853
01:04:25,256 --> 01:04:27,973
You're wonderful.

854
01:04:28,169 --> 01:04:31,945
You're wonderful.

855
01:04:32,234 --> 01:04:35,050
You've always been a wonderful boy.

856
01:04:35,243 --> 01:04:37,830
You know how much that it's meant to me?

857
01:04:38,027 --> 01:04:41,324
Be so proud of you, always.

858
01:04:41,516 --> 01:04:44,365
I know it.

859
01:05:10,390 --> 01:05:12,911
Don't worry, mother.

860
01:05:13,111 --> 01:05:15,730
Two weeks will go like an express train.

861
01:05:15,928 --> 01:05:17,074
You sure you're coming?

862
01:05:17,272 --> 01:05:18,221
Of course. I promise.

863
01:05:18,457 --> 01:05:20,246
You can even get
my room in the village for me.

864
01:05:20,601 --> 01:05:22,096
I'll get you the same
one you're there last time.

865
01:05:22,458 --> 01:05:24,368
The one with the balcony.

866
01:05:24,571 --> 01:05:30,268
Didn't I tell you
that compartment was quaranteened?

867
01:05:30,717 --> 01:05:31,611
I'm sorry, Madam.

868
01:05:31,804 --> 01:05:34,260
This compartment had to be closed up.

869
01:05:34,462 --> 01:05:35,989
I'll take you to the next cart forwards.

870
01:05:36,191 --> 01:05:38,974
That's good.
I'll be near the local motive.

871
01:05:39,167 --> 01:05:42,943
I'll take the box.

872
01:05:44,097 --> 01:05:45,820
Do we have two local motives
on our train?

873
01:05:46,017 --> 01:05:47,676
We usually get along with one.

874
01:05:47,874 --> 01:05:49,784
But I talked to the engineer.

875
01:05:49,987 --> 01:05:52,355
How about that one over there?
You can have two seats in there.

876
01:05:52,547 --> 01:05:54,752
He's traveling alone.

877
01:05:55,108 --> 01:05:56,483
Don't worry about it, Madam.

878
01:05:56,709 --> 01:05:57,538
I'll take good care of him.

879
01:05:57,733 --> 01:05:59,424
We leave in about a minute.

880
01:05:59,622 --> 01:06:01,859
Better hurry and get your seat.

881
01:06:02,054 --> 01:06:04,062
You'll see better if you sit over here.

882
01:06:04,263 --> 01:06:05,987
And if you get chilly,
you can put up the window.

883
01:06:06,216 --> 01:06:08,999
Yes, mother.

884
01:06:09,193 --> 01:06:14,050
Stephan. You know how I've
longed for you to being home.

885
01:06:14,411 --> 01:06:16,234
And now I can't even explain.

886
01:06:16,395 --> 01:06:19,712
I hope some day, very soon...
I'll be able to give you a reason.

887
01:06:20,076 --> 01:06:24,168
But now, you just have to believe
that it's for your own goo

888
01:06:24,366 --> 01:06:25,992
I don't mind going back so much.

889
01:06:26,222 --> 01:06:28,263
Especially when you're coming so soon.

890
01:06:28,623 --> 01:06:29,768
It'd be like two vocations.

891
01:06:29,968 --> 01:06:31,146
Alright, darling.

892
01:06:31,504 --> 01:06:34,472
I'll show you the new walk
we found since you're there last

893
01:06:34,673 --> 01:06:38,449
Better get out, lady.

894
01:06:42,643 --> 01:06:44,367
You'll write me often, won't you?

895
01:06:44,564 --> 01:06:50,895
Yes mother But I can't write very often.
We've only two weeks.

896
01:06:51,094 --> 01:06:56,792
Good-bye, mother. Two weeks.

897
01:07:29,474 --> 01:07:32,322
Make way, please.

898
01:07:32,515 --> 01:07:33,890
Make way, please.

899
01:07:34,084 --> 01:07:36,899
What happened?

900
01:07:37,189 --> 01:07:38,684
Someone hurt?

901
01:07:38,885 --> 01:07:40,129
No reason to get alarmed.

902
01:07:40,326 --> 01:07:41,570
They said that it's typhus.

903
01:07:41,766 --> 01:07:42,268
Typhus?

904
01:07:42,662 --> 01:07:47,398
Yes. Typhus on the train.

905
01:08:01,484 --> 01:08:01,986
Yes. Madam.

906
01:08:02,189 --> 01:08:04,294
Yes. Mr. Brown. Stephan Brown.

907
01:08:04,653 --> 01:08:09,411
Brown? One moment, please.

908
01:08:09,647 --> 01:08:11,055
Fritz!

909
01:08:11,375 --> 01:08:13,962
Um?

910
01:08:17,714 --> 01:08:20,562
Could you tell me has Mr. Brown
been here this evening?

911
01:08:20,915 --> 01:08:23,763
Oh, Mr. Brown is no longer
a customer of ours.

912
01:08:23,955 --> 01:08:25,417
Not for sometime.

913
01:08:25,780 --> 01:08:28,715
Mr. Brown these days
is more likely to be found in the Ritz.

914
01:08:28,917 --> 01:08:31,765
Thank you.

915
01:09:00,896 --> 01:09:01,790
Good evening, Madam.

916
01:09:01,984 --> 01:09:04,701
I still have nice flowers left.
I'm closing up.

917
01:09:04,896 --> 01:09:10,462
And I've saved you
a nice bouquet. Very cheap.

918
01:09:14,403 --> 01:09:18,147
I'll take those, the white ones.

919
01:09:18,501 --> 01:09:19,613
Don't bother wrapping them up.

920
01:09:19,813 --> 01:09:23,589
Doesn't matter.

921
01:10:07,157 --> 01:10:11,468
Now, drive.
Drive on!

922
01:10:34,909 --> 01:10:39,645
Stephan Brown. Is he in?

923
01:10:48,481 --> 01:10:51,297
Thank you.

924
01:11:36,817 --> 01:11:38,312
This is a surprise.

925
01:11:38,673 --> 01:11:41,195
But I assure you're a very happy one.

926
01:11:41,554 --> 01:11:46,826
John didn't prepare me
for such pleasant occassion.

927
01:11:47,188 --> 01:11:49,076
I thought last night...

928
01:11:49,268 --> 01:11:52,717
The darkness might've
been tricks with my eyes.

929
01:11:53,078 --> 01:11:55,599
You're even more
beautiful than I imagined.

930
01:11:55,959 --> 01:11:57,268
Very kind of you.

931
01:11:57,495 --> 01:12:00,595
This is just the hour
for a bit late supper.

932
01:12:00,792 --> 01:12:01,720
Or is it too late?

933
01:12:01,913 --> 01:12:03,637
Oh, it makes no different.
You're here.

934
01:12:03,833 --> 01:12:06,834
As far as I'm concerned,
all the clocks in the world will st

935
01:12:07,035 --> 01:12:08,759
Exuse me a moment.

936
01:12:08,955 --> 01:12:10,744
John!

937
01:12:11,132 --> 01:12:12,659
John, I'm sorry to send you out so late.

938
01:12:13,053 --> 01:12:15,060
Would you go out to the coners,
and get a few things.

939
01:12:15,261 --> 01:12:20,959
We're going to have supper.
The usual things.

940
01:12:25,696 --> 01:12:29,723
John makes life possible for
a hopelessly single man.

941
01:12:29,922 --> 01:12:32,443
She fascinates you, too!

942
01:12:32,674 --> 01:12:33,438
Do you remember...

943
01:12:33,634 --> 01:12:36,352
The Greek built the
Statue of God they didn't know.

944
01:12:36,548 --> 01:12:38,752
But hope someday would come to them.

945
01:12:39,108 --> 01:12:41,018
But mine happened to be a Goddess.

946
01:12:41,221 --> 01:12:43,523
And you've never found her?

947
01:12:43,878 --> 01:12:46,268
For years, I never woke in the morning,

948
01:12:46,663 --> 01:12:48,769
But I said to myself,

949
01:12:48,968 --> 01:12:53,704
Perhaps today she will come.
My life will be really to begin.

950
01:12:53,929 --> 01:12:57,247
Sometimes it seemed very near.

951
01:12:57,450 --> 01:13:03,049
But now I'm older, I know better.

952
01:13:03,693 --> 01:13:05,930
Even for yourself,
you don't play anymore?

953
01:13:06,125 --> 01:13:09,804
Oh, I remember last night,
you're kind of being interested...

954
01:13:09,998 --> 01:13:11,886
I forgot John locked
it when I went away.

955
01:13:12,079 --> 01:13:14,830
Nowadays, I'm away quite a lot of time.

956
01:13:15,024 --> 01:13:19,248
I'll ask him for the key
when he comes back.

957
01:13:19,441 --> 01:13:21,165
You wear very lovely.

958
01:13:21,362 --> 01:13:22,639
It's a beautiful dress.

959
01:13:22,834 --> 01:13:24,428
Thank you.

960
01:13:24,627 --> 01:13:27,530
How could you do that?
Give it up altogether.

961
01:13:27,892 --> 01:13:30,478
Well, if you're so curious,
I'll tell you.

962
01:13:30,837 --> 01:13:33,260
One night I came back to this room.

963
01:13:33,462 --> 01:13:35,884
I had given a concert like
all the others.

964
01:13:36,118 --> 01:13:38,737
Not bad, and not worse.

965
01:13:38,935 --> 01:13:41,903
Afterwards,
they said all the usual things.

966
01:13:42,105 --> 01:13:45,270
The things you say
when you are not really convinced.

967
01:13:45,465 --> 01:13:46,546
So, I happened to look into the mirror.

968
01:13:46,746 --> 01:13:49,300
This one here.

969
01:13:49,498 --> 01:13:51,921
The young protege was no longer young.

970
01:13:52,123 --> 01:13:55,255
Certainly wasn't perpetual.

971
01:13:55,453 --> 01:13:58,072
Since then, I found out a thing to do.

972
01:13:58,270 --> 01:14:02,046
More amuzing things.

973
01:14:06,817 --> 01:14:12,514
I knew last night. Didn't you?

974
01:14:27,847 --> 01:14:32,289
I haven't even
offered to fix you a drink.

975
01:14:32,489 --> 01:14:32,870
Stephan.

976
01:14:33,224 --> 01:14:35,200
Yes.

977
01:14:35,401 --> 01:14:38,020
I came here...
I have something to tell you.

978
01:14:38,218 --> 01:14:39,527
If it's something to do with you,
lm very interested.

979
01:14:39,883 --> 01:14:41,477
It has to do with us.

980
01:14:41,836 --> 01:14:44,684
We can't possibily
be serious this early in the morning.

981
01:14:44,908 --> 01:14:46,250
At least not without
a glass of champagne.

982
01:14:46,605 --> 01:14:49,923
Won't be a minute.

983
01:14:50,126 --> 01:14:53,608
Champagne tastes much better
after midnight, don't you think

984
01:14:53,807 --> 01:14:54,920
Much better.

985
01:14:55,280 --> 01:14:56,360
I've just came back from America.

986
01:14:56,561 --> 01:14:58,088
It's a fascinating country.

987
01:14:58,288 --> 01:14:59,598
The men are fond of money.

988
01:14:59,953 --> 01:15:02,255
And their wives... are fond of Europeans.

989
01:15:02,450 --> 01:15:04,109
Must have been a wonderful trip?

990
01:15:04,306 --> 01:15:08,847
Have you travelled a great deal?

991
01:15:09,044 --> 01:15:14,742
I couldn't get
you out of my mind all day.

992
01:15:15,030 --> 01:15:16,623
No, I don't believe you.

993
01:15:16,823 --> 01:15:18,579
If I only knew you're coming...

994
01:15:18,775 --> 01:15:19,823
To tell you the truth,

995
01:15:20,183 --> 01:15:22,606
I never dared to hope
that you could've managed so soon.

996
01:15:23,000 --> 01:15:25,903
But you're so cleaver,
you've arranged it so beautifully.

997
01:15:26,105 --> 01:15:29,205
You know, you're a very strange woman.

998
01:15:29,434 --> 01:15:30,383
Am I?

999
01:15:30,747 --> 01:15:35,833
Something you've said last night,
it keeps running through my

1000
01:15:36,029 --> 01:15:37,556
What was that?

1001
01:15:37,757 --> 01:15:42,199
I'll tell you in just a moment
as soon as I get the ice.

1002
01:15:42,399 --> 01:15:45,149
Are you getting lonely out there.

1003
01:15:45,343 --> 01:15:48,192
Very lonely.

1004
01:15:52,770 --> 01:15:55,039
I come to tell you about us.

1005
01:15:55,267 --> 01:15:58,082
To offer you my whole life.

1006
01:15:58,276 --> 01:16:03,974
But you didn't even remember me.

1007
01:16:40,145 --> 01:16:42,633
Can I take you somewhere, young lady?

1008
01:16:42,866 --> 01:16:45,517
Anywhere at all?

1009
01:16:45,715 --> 01:16:50,451
It makes no difference.

1010
01:17:10,139 --> 01:17:12,595
I don't remember where I went.

1011
01:17:12,795 --> 01:17:14,771
Time will pass me.

1012
01:17:14,972 --> 01:17:16,980
Not in days, or in hours.

1013
01:17:17,341 --> 01:17:21,051
But in the distance
that put between us.

1014
01:17:21,246 --> 01:17:24,542
Now I think again.
I went to my son.

1015
01:17:24,895 --> 01:17:27,198
But is was too late.

1016
01:17:27,392 --> 01:17:30,709
He died last night from typhus.

1017
01:17:30,913 --> 01:17:34,078
Without even knowing I was there.

1018
01:17:34,274 --> 01:17:36,696
Now I'm alone.

1019
01:17:36,931 --> 01:17:40,729
My head throbs,
and my temple are burning.

1020
01:17:40,965 --> 01:17:46,204
Perhaps God had been kind.
I, too, have caught the fever.

1021
01:17:46,406 --> 01:17:50,368
If this letter reaches you,
believe this...

1022
01:17:50,568 --> 01:17:54,344
That I love you now as
I've always loved you.

1023
01:17:54,697 --> 01:17:55,645
My life can be measured...

1024
01:17:55,849 --> 01:17:59,811
By the moments
that I've with you and our child.

1025
01:18:00,010 --> 01:18:03,492
If only you could've shared
those moments.

1026
01:18:03,691 --> 01:18:07,621
If only you could've recognized
what was always yours.

1027
01:18:07,820 --> 01:18:10,985
Could've found whar was never lost.

1028
01:18:11,182 --> 01:18:13,998
If only...

1029
01:19:54,158 --> 01:19:57,934
You remembered her?

1030
01:20:16,278 --> 01:20:19,093
Lisa...

1031
01:20:22,360 --> 01:20:25,012
Lisa...

1032
01:20:59,204 --> 01:21:02,980
Bring my things.

1033
01:21:30,221 --> 01:21:33,997
Ready, gentleman?

1034
01:21:36,527 --> 01:21:40,652
If only you could've recognized
what was always yours.

1035
01:21:40,944 --> 01:21:44,044
Could've found what was never lost...

